--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Repositories in home directory
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

~/git
	- git repository for git

~/quilt
	- git repository for Quilt, see http://savannah.nongnu.org/projects/quilt/
	- Quilt is a patch management system, rather than a source code management system.

~/mutt
	- Mercurial repository for mail client Mutt

~/linux
	- git repository for below repositories:
	  * origin        git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git
	  * linux-next    git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/next/linux-next.git
	  * linux-stable  git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/stable/linux-stable.git

~/Generate-GIT-send-mail-arguments
	- git repository for script that generates 'git send-email' arguments automatically
          by looking at the output generated by scripts/get_maintainers.pl.

~/sparse
	- git repository for Sparse

~/eudyptula-challenge
	- answers for Eudyptula Challenge

~/lktest
	- source code for testing linux kernel
	- pushed to GitHub.com

~/smatch
	- source code for Smatch project

~/openwrt
	- source code for OpenWrt project

~/systemd
	- source code for systemd project, which includes udev

~/kscope
	- source code for kscope project from:
	  svn checkout svn://svn.code.sf.net/p/kscope/code/trunk kscope


~/update_repo.sh
	- shell script for download source code from server


